items.checkin_comment: While this style (I believe) is best served cold, this 40 degree day warmed it up quicker than I could drink it. At this point I got the pepper coming through. Really subtle, but was quite tasty. All in all then, a nice refreshing beer for hot days!

Hazy and white like a winter storm, but best enjoyed on a warm sunny day. This specific style of wheat beer brings with it a subtle mix of spices and hops, giving it a distinct flavor with little bitterness. That's 5 different beers categorized as a Witbier. Try 5 more for Level 2!

items.checkin_comment: Contains Sichuan pepper & lime, apparently, & that might be what makes this witbier a more enjoyable beer than I usually find with wheat beers. I was due to drink this on 14/12 as part of the Beer Cartel Canvent, but didn’t because I usually hate these.
